A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing International Literacy Day, honoring the contributions of Trinity International
2 University of Ambassadors, and celebrating Dr. Jacqueline Mohair and Dr. Cheryl
3 Polote-Williamson; and for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, International Literacy Day, established by UNESCO and observed annually on
5 September 8, highlights the critical importance of literacy in fostering education, social
6 inclusion, and sustainable development across the globe; and
7 WHEREAS, literacy is a fundamental right that empowers individuals, strengthens
8 communities, and drives societal progress, and this day serves as an opportunity to address
9 global literacy challenges and advocate for inclusive learning opportunities; and
10 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia recognizes and celebrates the transformative work of Dr.
11 Jacqueline Mohair, founder of Trinity International University of Ambassadors, TIUA
12 School of Business, and Trinity International Chaplaincy Institute, for her lifelong dedication
13 to advancing education, leadership, and global advocacy through innovative programs; and
